Architecture & Background:
Traditional Rajasthani palace wall with hand-painted elephant motifs, pastel yellow and pink tones, carved wooden door with metal studs. Architectural symmetry preserved, murals crisp and undistorted, heritage textures clearly visible.
Lighting: Soft natural daylight, diffused sunlight from front-left, cinematic editorial lighting.
Balanced highlights and shadows, no harsh contrast, true-to-life skin tones, natural color temperature (~5200K).
High dynamic range, smooth tonal transitions.
Camera & Lens:
Full-frame DSLR/medium-format look
Lens: 35mm prime
Aperture: f/4 - f/5.6 (sharp from head to toe)
ISO 100
